The paper deals with algorithms designed to increase the effective dimension of binary sequences, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper also discusses the Kucera-Gacs theorem, which is a result in computational randomness (cs.CR) and uses techniques related to finite-state automata (cs.DS) and combinatorics (cs.DM). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.IT and cs.CC, followed by cs.DS, cs.CR, and cs.DM.
